        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="13" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/2–648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-09T19:00:00-05:00">February 9, 1948—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>215. Although Dept has no great confidence in Gen Chen Cheng Kai-min it would no
                    doubt be advantageous (Embtel 241 Feb 6) for Chinese to centralize purchases for
                    acquisition of military supplies. However Dept considers this administrative
                    matter for decision by Chinese.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
